segments.text: Yes, I'm pleased today to present to you David Perez, who is a nominee for the Ethics Elections Commission.

segments.text: My name is Andrea Scheele and I am the Executive Director of the Civil Service Commission for the City of Seattle and also for the Public Safety Civil Service Commission.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: I'm happy today to present Charlene McMillan as the nominee for Commissioner for the Civil Service Commission.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: McMillan has worked in labor and employee relations since 1994.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: She currently practices has her own private practice as an arbitrator and she has worked as a human resources professional.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: She also was a city of Seattle labor negotiator and employee relations advisor during her career.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: She holds a master's degree in public administration, and her degree is in business administration with a focus on human resources management.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: McMillan will bring to the Civil Service Commission her understanding of city operations, education.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_03

segments.text: She'll also bring her education, training, and experience in employee management and discipline, and her deep commitment to due process and equal justice in the adjudication of appeals that will be heard by the commission.

segments.text: I'm just extremely happy to present to you, Ms.
